## Stage 1: Copying Code

### Today's Mission

Welcome to your first MongoDB (NoSQL) program! Today, you'll create and run your very first program.

---

### Learning Goals

- Understand the basic structure of a MongoDB (NoSQL) program
- Learn how to compile/run MongoDB (NoSQL) code
- See your first program output 'Hello, World!'
- Get comfortable with your development environment

---

### Your Task

**Copy the following code EXACTLY as shown below into `main.js`**

```javascript
// MongoDB JavaScript shell script
print("Hello, World!");
```

---

### How to Run

**Method 1 (Vim - Recommended):**
```
<Space>r
```

**Method 2 (Terminal):**
```bash
mongo < script.js
```

**Expected output:**
```
Hello, World!
```

(Your actual output will vary based on the code example)

